{"id":4536,"title":"[Diagnostics of pneumothorax with ultrasound].","abstract":"The article deals with a method of pneumothorax diagnostics based on verification of four ultrasound sings--lung sliding absence, B-lines absence, lung pulse absence and lung point presence. Use of ultrasound allows to quickly diagnose a pneumothorax and to monitor the condition of pleural space. Introduction of the ultrasound methods into routine work ICU specialists can increase safety of patients.","date":"2014-12-31","categories":"Respiratory Tract Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25549490","annotations":[{"name":"Pneumothorax","weight":0.808804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pneumothorax"},{"name":"Ultrasound","weight":0.7968,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultrasound"},{"name":"Pleural cavity","weight":0.688708,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pleural_cavity"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.685738,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Medical diagnosis","weight":0.624518,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_diagnosis"},{"name":"Lung","weight":0.585738,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lung"},{"name":"Pulse","weight":0.52085,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pulse"},{"name":"Intensive care unit","weight":0.230656,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive_care_unit"},{"name":"Safety","weight":0.0495178,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Safety"},{"name":"Space","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space"},{"name":"Formal verification","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Formal_verification"},{"name":"Monitor (warship)","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monitor_(warship)"}]}
